@node main "Easy Setup Document."

        This  is  a  document  that will help you to setup a working
        gateway  using  MONALISA.  Read this carefuly and don't skip
        anything if you don't know what it means.

                                - - - - - - -

        Run   the  instalation  script  found  in  the  distribution
        archive.   You  will  need Commodore's Installer program for
        this.   If you don't have it, you easily find it in a public
        files library.

        Open  the  drawer  where  MONALISA  is  and  enter  @{"PKTGEN" link PKTGEN}'s
        sub-directory.   Click  twice  in  the 'Config PKTGen' icon.
        Using  your  text  editor, modify the defaults to match your
        system configuration.

        Choose  a  Fidonet  address  to be used as gateway.  You can
        choose  a  4D  (ie.  a Point) or a 3D address (ie.  a Node).
        Be  sure  that  that  address isn't already owned by someone
        else,  that  is,  no  one will ever call your Fido frontdoor
        using  it.   This address will be referred as @{"FFA" link FFA} (Fake Fido
        Address) from now on.

        Configure  your  Fido frontdoor to password protect the @{"FFA" link FFA}.
        This  is only for security reasons since actually you should
        never receive calls from such system.

        Configure  your Fidonet Mailer/Tosser to export the Echomail
        you  wish  to  gate  to the @{"FFA" link FFA}.  Take a note of the TAGNAME
        from the conferences you will be gating.  You will need this
        information to configure the Fido2UUCP module.

        Configure  your  Fidonet Mailer/Tosser to export all NetMail
        to  the  FFA  in NORMAL HOLD.  That is, NetMail files in the
        Outbount dir must have the address.OUT format.

        Choose  a  name  for  a  UUCP  system  that  will be used by
        UUCP2Fido  to gate Usenet articles to Fidonet.  This will be
        referred  as  @{"FUUN" link FUUN}.  Remember that this name can't have more
        than 7 chars.

        Configure  your  UUCP  package  to  accept  this  fake site.
        Password  protect  it  to prevent possible security attacks.
        In  AmigaUUCP 1.16, this is archieved adding an entry in the
        UULIB:L.Sys file.  Password protection depends of the method
        used  in each system to receive UUCP calls.  Usually you can
        do this by editing the UULIB:Passwd file.

        Editing   the  UULIB:Sys  file,  you  can  tell  UUCP  which
        conferences  you  want  to  gate  to  Fidonet.  Use the @{"FUUN" link FUUN}
        system  as  the  feed  site.   You can play around with many
        possible  configurations.   You can establish one or two way
        (Read/Write) conferences between Fidonet and Usenet.

        Enter  Fido2UUCP  sub-directory  and click the configuration
        the  program.  Remember the TAGNAMEs of the Fido conferences
        that  you  are gating to the FFA address and use them in the
        'Fido  conferences'  list.   Also, there is a sub-window for
        E-Mail  configuration.   By default, Fido2UUCP will not gate
        any NetMail until you configure it properly.  Read @{"Fido2UUCP" link "Monalisa:Documentation/Programs/Fido2UUCP/HOW_TO_USE"}
        documentation for more details.

        P.S.1  Remeber  to  match  the  "Gate  HostName"  with @{"FUUN" link FUUN},
        otherwise  you  may create feedback problems.  You may enter
        @{"FUUN" link FUUN} with domain here.

        P.S.2  If  you  want to gate NetMail as well, read @{"Fido2UUCP" link "Monalisa:Documentation/Programs/Fido2UUCP/HOW_TO_USE"}
        docs. to  see the meaning of the "E-Mail Gatename" field for
        each conference.

        Edit   the   file  MONALISA:Preferences/BounceMail.prefs  by
        clicking  twice  the 'Config BadMesgs' icon in the Fido2UUCP
        directory.   Just  change the example address (2:361/1.0) to
        your  system  address.   You need to change anything else if
        you don't know what it means yet.

        Enter  UUCP2Fido  sub-directory  and click the configuration
        program.  Remember which Usenet conferences you are going to
        gate  to  Fidonet  and  use these in the 'Usenet Newsgroups'
        list.   Remember  to  enter  the  @{"FUUN" link FUUN}  in the 'Gateway Sys'
        field.    UUCP2Fido   has   also  a  sub-window  for  E-Mail
        configuration.   By  default,  UUCP2Fido  will  not gate any
        E-Mail  to  Fidonet  until  you  edit  the Accept and Reject
        lists. Read @{"UUCP2Fido" link "Monalisa:Documentation/Programs/UUCP2Fido/HOW_TO_USE"} documentation for more details.

        You  will  also see an icon called "Config PKTGen E-Mail" in
        UUCP2Fido  sub-directory.   Click  this  icon  to  edit  the
        defaults  for  your system Origin Line and address that will
        be used when UUCP2Fido gates E-Mail to NetMail.

        If  you  are  going to gate E-Mail to Netmail, edit the file
        UULIB:Domain and add the following entries to it:

        *.@{"FUUN" link FUUN}                MF UU   @{"FUUN" link FUUN}
        *.@{"FUUN" link FUUN}.your.domain    MF UU   @{"FUUN" link FUUN}

        If  you  are running a 24H service, you will probably have a
        Cron  program  running.   You  can  program  the Cron to run
        MONALISA:Executables/Fido2UUCP/Tosser                    and
        MONALISA:Executables/UUCP2Fido/UUCP2Fido  as  many  times as
        you  wish  to have your convertion updated.  Optionally, you
        can  run some Scripts found in the Contributions drawer that
        will  basically  do  the  same  thing  but  can  be used via
        Workbench.

        To   undersand   better   how   MONALISA   works,  read  the
        documentation  from  each module.  This should help you with
        not-so-easy setups.

        This should do the job. Have fun!

      [ Fidonet is referred in this document as a technology and not ]
      [ as a Network.                                                ]

      [ It is expected that the user has some knowlegde with Fidonet ]
      [ and UUCP/Usenet.                                             ]

@endnode
@node FFA "Fake Fido Address"

        The  Fake  Fido  Address is the address used to gate your
        Fidonet messages to Usenet.
@endnode
@node PKTGEN "PKTGenerator"

        PKT-Generator  is, as the name suggests, a FidoNet Packet
        Generator.  In detail, you can use PktGen to send mail to
        other  systems,  to  your  system's  points  or  even  to
        yourself.  PktGen is able to send private NetMail as well
        as  public  conference messages.  PktGen respects all FSC
        standards  and  so  far,  I  haven't  found a mailer that
        couldn't import packets from it.
@endnode
@node FUUN "Fake UUCP System Name"

        The  Fake  UUCP  System  Name  is the site used to gate your
        Usenet articles to Fidonet messages and vice-versa.
@endnode
